# Evert Vorster reports gtk-doc requires Python for compilation
# Python is required by gnome-doc-utils

with version stable 1.18 1.17 1.16
with base    docbook-xml-4.5 docbook-xml-4.3 docbook-xsl gnome-doc-utils
with role    utility/editor
with trait   gnome library makej multilib-concurrent
with source  $GNOME_URL sources/gtk-doc/${VERSION:0:4}/gtk-doc-$VERSION.tar.xz
with info    last 20110919
with info    good 20120919
with info    home http://gtkspell.sourceforge.net
with info    cite 'DocBook documentation generator, may cause some sources to fail compilation
gtk-doc may cause some spells to fail during compilation!
GTK-Doc is used to document C code.
It is typically used to document the public API of
libraries, such as the GTK+ and Gnome libraries.
But it can also be used to document application code.'
